  "prompt": "Who are some of the famous programmers from India?",
  "response": "India has produced a remarkable number of talented programmers who have made significant contributions to the tech world. Here are some famous ones, categorized for better understanding:\n\n**Pioneers & Established Leaders:**\n\n*   **Vinod Dham:** Known as the \"Pentium Father\" for his pivotal role in developing the Intel Pentium processor. This revolutionized personal computing.\n*   **Arvind Panagariya:** While primarily an economist, Panagariya also has a deep understanding of technology. He served as the first Vice-Chairman of NITI Aayog and is known for his work on trade and development, often influenced by technological innovation.\n*   **Sabeer Bhatia:** Co-founder of Hotmail (later acquired by Microsoft), one of the first and most successful webmail services. He is a significant figure in the early days of the internet boom.\n\n**Entrepreneurs & Founders:**\n\n*   **Bhavish Aggarwal & Ankit Bhati:** Co-founders of Ola Cabs, a major ride-hailing company in India and internationally. They revolutionized transportation in India.\n*   **Ritesh Agarwal:** Founder and CEO of OYO Rooms, a global hospitality chain that transformed the budget hotel industry.\n*   **Vijay Shekhar Sharma:** Founder and CEO of Paytm, a leading digital payments and financial services company in India.\n*   **Deepinder Goyal:** Co-founder and CEO of Zomato, a prominent online food ordering and delivery platform.\n*   **Binny Bansal & Sachin Bansal:** Co-founders of Flipkart, one of India's largest e-commerce companies (later acquired by Walmart).\n*   **Naveen Tewari:** Founder and CEO of InMobi, a global mobile advertising platform.\n*   **Girish Mathrubootham:** Founder and CEO of Freshworks, a SaaS company providing customer engagement software.\n*   **Sriharsha Majety, Rahul Jaimini, Nandan Reddy:** Co-founders of Swiggy, a popular online food ordering and delivery platform.\n\n**Researchers & Academics:**\n\n*   **Raj Reddy:** Turing Award winner (1994) for his pioneering work in artificial intelligence and robotics. He is a professor at Carnegie Mellon University.\n*   **Prabhakar Raghavan:** Senior Vice President at Google and leads Google Search, Assistant, Geo (Maps and Local), Ads, Commerce, and Payments products.\n*   **Umesh Vazirani & Vijay Vazirani:** Renowned professors at UC Berkeley and Georgia Tech, respectively. They are known for their work in quantum computing, algorithms, and theoretical computer science.\n*   **Manindra Agrawal, Neeraj Kayal, Nitin Saxena:** Known for the AKS primality test, a deterministic polynomial-time algorithm for determining whether a number is prime. This was a breakthrough in number theory and theoretical computer science.\n\n**Software Architects & Engineers (Often Less Publicly Known, but Crucial):**\n\n*   While many talented Indian programmers work behind the scenes at major tech companies, their individual names are often less widely known.  However, their contributions are immense. They are essential in building and maintaining complex software systems at companies like Google, Microsoft, Amazon, Facebook/Meta, and many others.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Defining \"Famous\":** Fame can be subjective. Some individuals are widely recognized within the tech industry, while others are more known to the general public.  This list tries to encompass both.\n*   **Diversity of Contributions:** This list highlights various roles - from founding companies to making fundamental research contributions.  All are critical to the advancement of technology.\n*   **Dynamic Field:** The field of computer science and programming is constantly evolving.  Many more talented programmers are emerging from India every year.\n\nThis list is not exhaustive, but it represents a good starting point for exploring the contributions of Indian programmers to the world of technology. You can research these individuals and their work further to get a deeper understanding of their impact.\n",
